The lectures, seminars and practices of the course give the overview of the impulses, components, phases and methods of the performance and composition of the art piece by different lectures of perfoming arts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is acquire the basics of performing arts' functioning and different theories and practices about conception, composition, rehearsing process, creative enviroment and production.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course student:
-is able to describe and analyze the creative impulse and idea in a context of the performance;
-is able to describe and analyze the production, rehearsing process and audience's reception of the performance;
-knows theoretical basics of performing arts;
-knows the specialities of the different performance's components (performer, room/ design, lightning design, sound design, video etc) -is able to create composed piece of art in basic level.
